article.description: B.J. Glasford scored a career-high 24 points on 11-of-17 shooting and Divine Myles scored 10 points with 11 rebounds to help lead Stetson to an 83-71 win on Monday night against Green Bay.
article.headline: Glasford's career best sends Stetson past Green Bay 83-71
article.linkText: Glasford's career best sends Stetson past Green Bay 83-71
article.story: GREEN BAY, Wis. -- B.J. Glasford scored a career-high 24 points on 11-of-17 shooting and Divine Myles scored 10 points with 11 rebounds to help lead Stetson to an 83-71 win on Monday night against Green Bay. Myles made a layup and a 3-pointer for a 13-9 lead and Stetson never trailed again. That was part of a 17-4 run in which Myles scored nine points. Stetson led 51-31 at halftime and kept the double-digit lead throughout the second half. Stetson (5-3) also got 13 points from Kenny Aninye and 11 from Luke Doyle. The Hatters were 36-for-74 shooting (48.6 percent), including 10 of 24 from 3-point range, and 1 for 2 from the free-throw line. Khalil Small scored 19 points on 7-for-10 shooting, including three 3-pointers, for Green Bay (2-3) and Trevian Bell added 13 points.
